---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Support"
  description="Get support for Go Bananas. Contact info for testers, bug reports, feature requests, and feedback."
  path="/support"
>
  <section class="container-quiet page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Go Bananas</a></p>
    <h1 class="page-title">Support</h1>
    <p class="page-meta">Bug reports, feature requests, and beta access.</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="section-rule" />

  <article class="container-quiet section prose">
    <h2>How to reach us</h2>
    <p>
      Email{' '}
      <a href="mailto:feedback@bananascanner.com">feedback@bananascanner.com</a>{' '}
      with bug reports, feature requests, or anything else. Replies usually
      come within a few days.
    </p>

    <h2>Reporting a misclassification</h2>
    <p>
      If the app called a banana the wrong ripeness stage, that's the most
      useful feedback we can get. Two-step process:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Screenshot the result screen.</strong> The bottom of that
        screen has a small diagnostic block showing the hue values our
        classifier saw. That's the data we use to recalibrate.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Email the screenshot</strong> to{' '}
        <a href="mailto:feedback@bananascanner.com">feedback@bananascanner.com</a>{' '}
        with a quick note on what stage you'd call the banana yourself.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Beta access</h2>
    <p>
      Go Bananas is in beta on both iOS (TestFlight) and Android (Google
      Play internal testing). If you want in,{' '}
      <a href="mailto:feedback@bananascanner.com?subject=Go%20Bananas%20beta">email us</a>{' '}
      and mention which platform.
    </p>

    <h2>Permissions and data</h2>
    <p>
      Everything runs on your device. Nothing leaves your phone. See the{' '}
      <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-head {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
  }

  .page-meta {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section {
    padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }
</style>
